CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. 13, reads: "Love's Labor's Lost... Sometimes Home is Where the Heart Remains - Sold by Sheriff - This shambling remains of a home owned b a Pullman porter named Robinson and his wife at 630 Duff St. Upon their death the property was left to a niece in New Jersey.  The house, with awnings was sold at a sheriff's sale."
TitMainTitle: Two two-story houses, 630 Duff Street, Hill District
